AES-128-CTR single block: encrypt a 16-byte plaintext block under a
16-byte key and a 16-byte counter block. Counter mode turns the AES
block cipher into a stream cipher: keystream = AES-128(counter, key),
ciphertext = plaintext XOR keystream. The counter block is the IV seen
as a 128-bit big-endian integer; block N uses counter = IV + N
(incremented by the caller). CTR is its own inverse, so the same rule
decrypts. This is the encryption half of AES-128-GCM.
Single rule ctr_block(plaintext, key, counter, which) returns one byte.
